# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# Copy values into Vercel (frontend) and Render (backend) dashboards.
# Do NOT commit real secrets to git.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VERCEL (Frontend) — Project Settings → Environment Variables
# Root Directory: frontend
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Variable name              | Example value
# ---------------------------|----------------------------------------------
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL        | https://document-extraction-api.onrender.com
#
# Use your actual Render backend URL (no trailing slash).

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RENDER (Backend) — Web Service → Environment
# Root Directory: backend
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Variable name              | Example value
# ---------------------------|----------------------------------------------
# MONGO_URI                  | mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/...
# OPENAI_API_KEY             | sk-...  (or Azure key)
# FRONTEND_URL               | https://your-app.vercel.app
# CORS_ORIGINS               | https://your-app.vercel.app  (optional if FRONTEND_URL set)
#
# Azure OpenAI only (leave OPENAI_ENDPOINT unset for openai.com):
# OPENAI_ENDPOINT            | https://your-resource.openai.azure.com/
# OPENAI_API_VERSION         | 2024-12-01-preview
# OPENAI_GPT_DEPLOYMENT      | gpt-4o
#
# OpenAI.com only:
# OPENAI_MODEL               | gpt-4o
#
# Render low-memory (512MB) — required for free tier:
# OCR_LOW_MEMORY             | true
# OCR_WARMUP_ON_STARTUP      | false
# Build command              | pip install -r requirements-render.txt
#
# Optional:
# MONGO_DB_NAME              | document_extraction
# MONGO_COLLECTION_NAME      | extractions
# PYTHON_VERSION             | 3.11.11  (or use runtime.txt)
# OCR_ENABLE_TROCR           | true  (only if instance has 2GB+ RAM)
